prompt:
You describe ONE pedestrian for person re-identification. Describe ONLY the person.

Output EXACTLY TWO LINES.

LINE 1 (semicolon-separated key=value; use EXACT tokens below):
gender=male|female|unknown;
top_color=black|white|gray|red|orange|yellow|green|blue|purple|brown|pink|unknown;
top_type=tee|shirt|blouse|hoodie|sweater|jacket|coat|dress|none|unknown;
sleeve=long|short|sleeveless|unknown;
bottom_color=black|white|gray|red|orange|yellow|green|blue|purple|brown|pink|unknown;
bottom_type=jeans|trousers|shorts|skirt|dress|none|unknown;
bottom_length=long|knee|short|unknown;
shoes_color=black|white|gray|red|orange|yellow|green|blue|purple|brown|pink|unknown;
shoes_type=sneakers|boots|loafers|heels|sandals|unknown;
bag_color=black|white|gray|red|orange|yellow|green|blue|purple|brown|pink|none|unknown;
bag_type=backpack|shoulder|hand|waist|none|unknown;
headwear=cap|hood|hat|none|unknown;
hair=short|long|ponytail|bald|covered|unknown;
accessories=glasses|mask|scarf|watch|none;
pattern=solid|stripes|plaid|logo|text|other|none;
distinctive=<≤5 words clothing/accessory cue only>

LINE 2 (EXACTLY three cues; noun phrases only; join with " | "):
<cue1> | <cue2> | <cue3>

Rules:
- Use ONLY the tokens shown. Never write alternations (e.g., "black|white") or slashes.
- If dress is visible, set bottom_type=dress and top_type=none; set bottom_length accordingly.
- If unknown, write unknown (not blank).
- DISTINCTIVE and cues must be clothing/pattern/logo/accessory terms. No actions, background, or verbs.
- Use "tee" (not t-shirt/tshirt). Map slippers→sandals.
- Keep each cue ≤3 words. Examples: "red backpack", "white logo", "yellow stripes".
